  "market_context": "ETH on the 4-hour chart in a broadly bullish sequence around July 2023, with price climbing from ~34,862 through ~35,250 and continuing higher. Analyst walks candle by candle through how each 4H candle interacts with the prior candle's high and low.",
  "key_observation": "Each 4H candle either displaces and closes outside the prior candle's range (continuation, anticipate next prior high/low as draw on liquidity) or sweeps it and closes back inside (reversal framed toward the opposite side of the prior candle).",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Establish that, unless price consolidates indefinitely, it must reach either the previous candle's high or low, so these levels serve as draw on liquidity.",
    "Step 2: Note that if price cannot displace and close outside the previous candle's high/low, a reversal back into the range toward the opposite side can be framed.",
    "Step 3: On ETH 4H, observe the first candle take the previous candle's high, so anticipate the current high being taken next.",
    "Step 4: Next candle fails to displace/close outside, so flip bias and anticipate the previous candle's low as the next draw.",
    "Step 5: Price barely fails to take that previous low; bias is maintained and the next previous high is then targeted.",
    "Step 6: Continue iterating candle by candle — take previous high → can't close out → look for previous low; take previous low → can't close out → look for previous high.",
    "Step 7: At an inside bar, default to continuation of the prevailing uptrend and look for the previous candle's high.",
    "Step 8: When a candle closes outside the previous candle's range with displacement, anticipate continuation toward the next previous high (or low in bearish case).",
    "Step 9: Acknowledge cases where bias is invalidated (e.g., expected a low but high gets taken) and adjust to the new previous high/low draw.",
    "Step 10: Conclude that this previous-candle framework provides a reliable draw on liquidity that can then be confirmed with lower-timeframe entries (1H, 30m, 15m)."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Previous candle high/low on the 4H is a simple but powerful tool to frame intraday bias: closure outside = continuation toward the next prior high/low, closure back inside after a sweep = reversal toward the opposite side. Won't always be correct, but provides a consistent, reliable draw on liquidity.",
